# Skill routing for {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Default rule
Use the smallest skill or role that materially improves the current task. Do not route to research, documentation, security, or hooks flows unless the task justifies them.

## Core routing
- `developer` handles default implementation flow
- `test-engineer` handles test-specific work
- `planner` handles explicit planning when present

## Rigorous-only routing
- `context-researcher` for multi-file context mapping
- `architecture-synthesizer` for architecture-first synthesis
- `critical-judge` for destructive review
- `plan-verifier` for conformance governance

## Optional bundle routing
- research skills -> only when repository reading is insufficient
- documentation skills -> only when parity, ADRs, or technical text quality matter
- security skills -> only for security-sensitive surfaces or evidence-backed release gates
